<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retainer ring on the front auxiliary drive gear, snap ring groove facing the hub
                and away from the gear teeth (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13015g6">Figure 166</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13015g6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13015g6" filename="../figg13/G13015g6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 166. Install Retainer Ring on Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the front auxiliary drive gear bearing on the hub, bearing snap ring facing the groove
                in the retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13015g7">Figure 167</hotlnk>). Press the bearing on the gear with the snap ring in the
                groove of the retainer ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13015g7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13015g7" filename="../figg13/G13015g7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 167. Start Front Auxiliary Drive Gear Bearing on Hub</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring in the groove of the gear hub to retain the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13015g8">Figure 168</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13015g8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13015g8" filename="../figg13/G13015g8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 168. Install Snap Ring in Gear Hub Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer retainer ring, grooved side down (inset,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13015g9">Figure 169</hotlnk>), with a flanged driver.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13015g9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13015g9" filename="../figg13/G13015g9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 169. Install Outer Retainer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
